&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Extraordinary Children. An extraordinary career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great Ormond Street Hospital: Nurse Recruitment Virtual Open Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday 30th November 2020: 10.00 – 11.30&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note; This is an advertisement only and not a vacancy so please&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;do not&lt;/span&gt;submit an application form.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to be offering this virtual open day event to give you an insight into the various opportunities available at GOSH. Whether you are planning to start your nursing career with us next year, or you are an experienced nurse looking to progress and realise your career ambitions, we welcome you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come along to…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- take a virtual tour of the hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- hear our people share their career journeys&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- learn what educational support we provide&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- see what staff benefits we offer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- take part in a live virtual Q&amp;A session&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See what opportunities we have for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit your questions for the Q&amp;A during the booking process to ensure we can answer them in the most helpful way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Book your place now:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to book yourself onto the event by visiting the Eventbrite website and searching for&lt;strong&gt;GOSH Virtual Nurse Recruitment Open Day.&lt;/strong&gt;Alternatively, the weblink can be found in the &quot;Additional Information&quot; link in the attachments sections of this page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any other nursing queries please contact:&lt;strong&gt;nursing.workforce@gosh.nhs.uk.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
